  {
    id: "01-14",
    title: "Standard Procedure (Finale)",
    summary: "In the Act 1 finale, investigators expose the hypocrisy of 'standard procedure'—bureaucratic obstacles protect a wealthy predator, while street-level enforcement requires only a hunch. As the perpetrator walks free and a compliant judge is appointed, the ensemble reveals how procedural justice is weaponized, leaving the audience questioning if resolution is possible.",
    characters: "Ronnie, Tammy, Ash, Cammy, Press, Ensemble",
    hasMusic: true,
    youtubeId: "YBeARM-lNeo",
    script: [
      { type: 'musical-number', speaker: `SONG`, text: `[STANDARD PROCEDURE - Full cast number]` },
      { type: 'stage-direction', text: `Podium. Flags. Cameras. RONNIE steps to the podium. Applause from staffers and press. TAMMY stands slightly behind and to the side. RONNIE smiles broadly.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `Thank you. Thank you very much. Today we're making an important announcement for the administration and for the country.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `As you know, the Department of Justice has been working very hard — tremendous pressure, tremendous attacks, frankly — from people who don't like the work we're doing and don't like the results we’re getting. But we keep winning. And when you keep winning, you need very good lawyers. The best lawyers.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `And today I'm pleased to announce the appointment of Tammy Caldwell as Solicitor General of the United States.` },
      { type: 'stage-direction', text: `Applause. RONNIE gestures toward Tammy.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `Tammy comes to us from the Southern District of New York, where she has served with distinction after earlier work in Alabama. A tremendous record. Very tough. Very sharp. A lot of people in Washington like to talk about legal theory and constitutional interpretation and all of these big words. Tammy actually understands them.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `And more importantly — she understands what this administration is trying to do for the American people. That’s not always easy to find. Some lawyers, they want to fight the government. Some lawyers want to fight the president. Some lawyers wake up in the morning and say, “How do I stop the administration today?” We’ve seen a lot of that.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `But Tammy has shown something very rare in Washington. Alignment. She understands the legal vision of this administration and the direction we're taking the country. And frankly — it’s nice to have someone on our side for a change.` },
      { type: 'stage-direction', text: `Some laughter in the room. RONNIE continues.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `Now people say, “Why Tammy?” And there are a lot of reasons. First of all, she’s very talented. Very talented. Second — we need more women in positions like this. We really do. I looked around the room the other day and I said, “Where are the women lawyers?” And somebody said, “Well, sir, we have Tammy.” And I said, “Good. Let’s get Tammy up here.”` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `But in all seriousness, she’s earned it. She’s tough, she’s loyal, and she understands that when this administration sets a legal strategy, the job is to carry it forward. That’s the job. And she'll do it very well.` },
      { type: 'stage-direction', text: `RONNIE glances back at Tammy.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `We've had some people in government who think their job is to question leadership. To slow things down. To ask whether the president is right. That’s not the job. The job is to win. And Tammy understands winning.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `So we're very excited about this appointment. I think she’s going to be tremendous. Just tremendous.` },
      { type: 'stage-direction', text: `He gestures toward her. Suddenly two aides rush forward. ASH and CAMMY, speaking almost simultaneously.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `ASH`, text: `Sir—` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `CAMMY`, text: `Mr. President—` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `ASH`, text: `We need to speak with you—` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `CAMMY`, text: `Immediately.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `Now?` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `ASH`, text: `Yes, sir.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `CAMMY`, text: `It’s urgent. It can't wait. We need a moment.` },
      { type: 'stage-direction', text: `A beat. The room goes quiet. RONNIE looks from them to the cameras. Then back to them. RONNIE forces a smile.` },
      { type: 'dialogue', speaker: `RONNIE`, text: `Excuse me for just a moment.` },
      { type: 'stage-direction', text: `Lights shift. End scene.` }
    ]
  }
